<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2010/01/25/ajax-simplifications-in-spring-3-0">Ajax Simplifications in Spring 3.0</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Keith Donald</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2010-01-25 07:56:00.0">January 25, 2010</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="304" href="/blog/2010/01/25/ajax-simplifications-in-spring-3-0#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>In my <a href="http://blog.springsource.com/2009/12/21/mvc-simplifications-in-spring-3-0/">last entry</a>, I walked you through several enhancements in Spring 3 for web application development. A number of you expressed interest in a follow-up entry focused on Ajax remoting. Spring 3 provides a lot in this area to take advantage of. Read on, and I’ll walk you through it.</p>
<h2>Spring and Ajax Overview</h2>
<p>For the purposes of this article, when I say Ajax, I’m talking about the web browser’s ability to communicate with a web server asynchronously using JavaScript. On the server-side, Spring provides the programming model for defining web services, including services consumed by JavaScript clients. On the client-side, nobody rolls their own Ajax framework these days, either. Most use an established JavaScript framework such as <a href="https://www.jquery.com">jQuery</a> or <a href="https://dojotoolkit.org">Dojo</a>. </p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2010/01/25/ajax-simplifications-in-spring-3-0">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
