<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2010/01/19/introduction-to-spring-roo-screencast">Introduction To Spring Roo Screencast</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Stefan Schmidt</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2010-01-19 20:00:00.0">January 19, 2010</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="303" href="/blog/2010/01/19/introduction-to-spring-roo-screencast#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>After our mad dash to the final release of Spring Roo 1.0.0 on New Year’s Eve, many users have asked for an introductory screencast.<br></p>
<p><br>In this 5 minute screencast you will see how to:<br></p>
<ul>
<br>
<li>Develop a simple “contact manager application” using the Roo shell</li>
<br>
<li>Import and edit the project our free IDE, <a href="http://www.springsource.com/products/sts">SpringSource Tool Suite</a> (STS)</li>
<br>
<li>Run the Roo-provided integration tests in STS</li>
<br>
<li>Modify the application and understand ITD round-trip support</li>
<br>
<li>Deploy to your IDE’s web container</li>
<br>
<li>Use the scaffolded web user interface</li>
<br>
<li>“Push-in refactor” to move source code between Java source files and ITDs</li>
<br>
<li>Remove Roo from the project</li>
<br>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
